Elizabeth Warren na "tunani sosai" kan tsayawa takarar shugaban kasa a 2020, in ji Sanata daga Massachusetts
Sanata Elizabeth Warren daga Massachusetts ta ce a ranar Asabar tana "tunani sosai" kan yadda za ta yi takarar shugaban kasa bayan zaben da aka yi a tsakiyar shekara.
A wani taron karamar hukuma a Holyoke, Massachusetts, Warren ta tabbatar da cewa tana tunanin shiga zaben.
"Lokaci ya yi da mata za su je Washington don gyara lalacewar gwamnati, kuma hakan ya haɗa da mace a matsayi mafi girma", in ji ta, a cewar jaridar siyasa ta The Hill.
"Bayan 6 ga Nuwamba, zan yi tunani sosai game da neman takarar shugaban kasa".
Warren ya yi wa Shugaba Donald Trump magana a taron da aka yi a fadar garin, yana mai cewa yana "ja da wannan kasa a hanyar da ba ta dace ba".
"Ina matukar damuwa da abin da Donald Trump ke kawowa a dimokiradiyya", in ji ta.
Warren ta yi magana a fili game da Trump da kuma Brett Kavanaugh, wanda ya yi takarar shugabancin kasar a kotun koli.
A cikin wata tweet a ranar Juma'a, Warren ya ce "a bayyane yake, dole ne mu jira binciken FBI kafin mu yi zabe".
Amma wani bincike da aka fitar a ranar Alhamis ya nuna cewa yawancin magoya bayan Warren sun ce bai kamata ta tsaya takara ba a shekarar 2020.
Kashi hamsin da takwas na masu jefa kuri'a a Massachusetts sun ce bai kamata a zabi sanata ba, a cewar wani bincike da Cibiyar Bincike ta Siyasa ta Jami'ar Suffolk da Boston Globe suka yi.
