Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da 'tsoratar da' 'yan kasar da 'tallan farfaganda'
Mako guda bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka, inda ta yaba wa amfanin cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
A kwanakin baya, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni da wani shafi da aka biya na jaridar China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa, bayan ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wani zargi da China ta musanta.
Trump ya zargi Beijing da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, kamar yadda jami'an Amurka suka ruwaito ta Reuters, ya nuna sabon mataki a cikin wani yunkuri na kara matsa lamba daga Washington kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su saka tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna cikin faɗaɗa yaƙin cinikayya, inda suka ɗora wa juna haraji masu yawa.
Hukuncin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya ya kasance ne musamman don cin zarafin masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, kamar yadda masana na China da na Amurka suka ce.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma a baya gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce China ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni illa.
"China", kamar yadda Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani labari a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register na ranar Lahadi, "yanzu tana ninka barazanar ta wajen buga tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin jaridarmu mai 'yanci".
"Ta wajen yaɗa wannan farfagandar, gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma 'yancin 'yan jarida, al'adar da aka daɗe ana kiyayewa a Amirka ta wajen saka talla da aka biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A wani bangare kuma, za ka ga muryoyin masu saɓani a banza a wani shagon sayar da kayayyaki a tsakiyar birnin Beijing, kuma ba za ka ga ainihin ra'ayoyi da mutane na kasar Sin suke da su ba game da matsalar tattalin arziki, domin kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa "ɗaya daga cikin manyan jaridun kasar Sin ta ƙi buga labarinta", kamar dai ba ta ce daga wace jarida ta fito ba.
Masu sharhi sun ce, saboda matsalar Kavanaugh, 'yan Republican sun yi watsi da mata masu zabe a lokacin da ake shirin gudanar da zaben,
Da yake manyan 'yan Republican sun yi wa Brett Kavanaugh, wanda ke neman zama babban alkalin kotun tarayya, garkuwa, suna kare shi daga zargin cin zarafin mata, manazarta sun yi gargadin cewa hakan zai yi musu illa, musamman ma a tsakanin mata, a lokacin zaben da ke tafe.
An samu tashin hankali a kan wannan batu kuma yawancin 'yan Republican sun riga sun nuna cewa suna son ci gaba da jefa kuri'a.
"Ba za a iya canja waɗannan abubuwa ba", in ji Grant Reeher, farfesa a fannin siyasa a Makarantar Maxwell ta Jami'ar Syracuse, ga wata jarida da ta fito a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana mamakin ko ƙoƙarin da Sanata Jeff Flake (Republican, Arizona) ya yi na neman a yi bincike na FBI a lokacin ƙarshe zai isa ya gamsar da masu jefa kuri'a.
"Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru jiya ba, ba za su manta da shi gobe ba, kuma ba za su manta da shi ba a watan Nuwamba", in ji Karine Jean-Pierre, babban mai ba da shawara kuma kakakin kungiyar masu ci gaba ta MoveOn a ranar Juma'a, a cewar jaridar Washington, D.C.
A safiyar Juma'a masu zanga-zanga sun yi ihu suna cewa "November yana zuwa!" a yayin zanga-zangar da suka yi a zauren majalisar dattawa yayin da 'yan Republican da ke kula da kwamitin shari'a suka zabi amincewa da takarar Kavanaugh, duk da shaidar Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, in ji Mic.
"Himma da himma ga 'yan Democrat za su kai wani matsayi mai girma", in ji Stu Rothenberg, wani mai sharhi kan siyasa, ga shafin labarai.
"Mutane suna cewa ya riga ya yi yawa, kuma gaskiya ne.
Amma za ta iya ƙaruwa, musamman tsakanin mata masu jefa ƙuri'a a cikin ƙauyuka da kuma tsakanin matasa masu jefa ƙuri'a, masu shekaru 18 zuwa 29, waɗanda sau da yawa ba sa jefa ƙuri'a ko da ba su yarda da shugaban ba".
Ko da kafin Ford ta ba da shaida a fili, inda ta kara bayyana zargin ta na cin zarafin dan takarar kotun koli, manazarta sun nuna cewa za a iya samun koma baya idan 'yan Republican suka dage da nadin.
"Wannan ya zama rikice-rikice ga Jam'iyyar Republican", in ji Michael Steele, tsohon shugaban jam'iyyar Republican, a farkon makon da ya gabata, kamar yadda NBC News ta ruwaito.
"Ba wai kawai batun zaben kwamitin ba ne, ko kuma na karshe ko Kavanaugh zai je kotu, amma kuma batun yadda 'yan Republican suka yi da kuma yadda suka bi da ita", in ji Guy Cecil, darektan Priorities USA, wani rukuni da ke taimaka wa 'yan Democrat su samu zabe, a kan tashar labarai.
Amma, jama'ar Amirka sun nuna sun rarrabu a kan wanda za su yarda da shi bayan shaidar Ford da Kavanaugh, tare da wani karamin rinjaye da ke goyon bayan na biyun.
Wani sabon bincike na YouGov ya nuna cewa kashi 41 cikin 100 na masu amsa sun tabbata ko kuma sun yi imani da shaidar Ford, kuma kashi 35 cikin 100 sun tabbata ko kuma sun yi imani da Kavanaugh.
Bugu da ƙari, kashi 38 cikin ɗari sun ce suna ganin Kavanaugh ya yi ƙarya ko kuma wataƙila ya yi ƙarya a lokacin da yake ba da shaida, yayin da kashi 30 cikin ɗari suka ce haka ne game da Ford.
