An girmama wani limami na Cocin Ingila wanda ya sami lambar Victoria Cross a lokacin yakin duniya na farko a matsayin soja a garin da aka haife shi shekaru 100 bayan haka.
Lt. Col, Reverend Bernard Vann ya sami lambar yabo ne a sakamakon harin da aka kai a Bellenglise da Lehaucourt a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918.
Amma, wani ɗan bindiga ya kashe shi bayan kwana huɗu, kuma bai san cewa ya sami babban gata a yaƙin ba.
'Ya'yansa biyu sun yi wa'azin ranar Asabar a wani bikin tunawa da shi a Rushden, Northamptonshire.
Ɗaya daga cikin jikokin, Michael Vann, ya ce "ainihin alama ce" cewa an buɗe dutsen daidai shekara 100 bayan da kakansa ya yi nasara.
A ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918, Lt. Col. Vann ya ja-goranci rundunarsa a kan Canal de Saint-Quentin "cikin hazo mai-zafi, a ƙarƙashin wuta mai-zafi na bindigogi da na bindigogi".
Daga baya ya ruga zuwa layin wuta, ya jagoranci layin gaba kafin ya gudu zuwa bindiga shi kaɗai, ya kashe mambobi uku na rukunin.
An kashe Laftanar Kanar Vann a hannun wani dan Jamus mai bindiga a ranar 4 ga watan Oktoba, 1918, fiye da wata daya kafin karshen yakin.
Michael Vann, mai shekara 72, ya ce ayyukan kakansa "wani abu ne da na sani ba zan taɓa ganewa ba, amma kuma abin da ke sa ni tawali'u".
Shi da ɗan'uwansa Dr. James Vann sun kuma kafa wani abin tunawa bayan bikin da ƙungiyar matasa ta Brentwood Imperial Youth Band ta gudanar.
Michael Vann ya ce "ya ji daɗi sosai da ya samu damar taka rawa a wannan bikin" kuma ya daɗa cewa "taimakon mutane da yawa ne yake nuna ƙarfin hali na jarumi na gaskiya".
