Nigel Farage ya yi alkawarin "karfafa rundunar 'yan kasa" a wani zanga-zanga a taron jam'iyyar Conservative Party a yau.
Tsohon shugaban Ukip ya ce 'yan siyasa su ji "zafin" masu shakkar kudin Turai, yayin da daya daga cikin 'yan majalisar Theresa May ya ba da shawarar ya ba shi jagorancin tattaunawar da EU.
Dan majalisa mai ra'ayin mazan jiya Peter Bone ya shaida wa masu halartar gangamin na Birmingham cewa Birtaniya za ta 'shafe' idan Mr Farage ya kasance ministan Brexit.
Amma kalubalen da May ke fuskanta wajen sulhunta manyan bangarorin da ke da saɓani ya bayyana ne daga 'yan adawa biyu masu goyon bayan Remain da ke halartar wani taron zanga-zanga na daban a birnin na Brexit.
Firayim Ministan na fama da ci gaba da yarjejeniyar ta Chequers yayin da masu goyon bayan Brexit, Remain da EU ke kai mata hari.
Mutanen da suke goyon bayanta sun nace cewa za ta ci gaba da kokarin cimma yarjejeniya da Brussels duk da rashin nasarar da ta fuskanta, ta haka za ta tilasta wa masu shakkar kudin Turai da kuma jam'iyyar Labour su zabi tsakanin shirin ta da kuma 'hargitsi'.
Bone ya ce a taron Leave Means Leave a Solihull cewa yana son "jefar da Chequers cikin kwandon shara".
Ya ba da shawarar cewa Farage ya kamata a sanya shi a matsayin mai gadon sarauta kuma a ba shi alhakin tattaunawar da Brussels.
"Da a ce ya kashe aikin, da mun gama shi yanzu", in ji Bone.
Dan majalisa na Wellingborough ya kara da cewa: "Zan goyi bayan Brexit, amma dole ne mu jefa Chequers cikin kwandon shara".
Da yake bayyana rashin amincewarsa da EU, ya ce: "Ba mu yi yaƙi a yaƙe-yaƙe biyu na duniya ba domin mu zama marasa ƙarfi.
Muna son mu kafa dokokinmu a ƙasarmu".
Bone ya yi watsi da ra'ayin cewa ra'ayin jama'a ya canza tun bayan zaben raba gardama na 2016: "Tunanin cewa mutanen Burtaniya sun canza ra'ayinsu kuma suna son ci gaba da kasancewa cikin EU ba gaskiya bane".
'Yar jam'iyyar Brexit mai ra'ayin Conservative Andrea Jenkyns ta shiga cikin wannan gangamin, inda ta shaida wa manema labarai cewa: "Ina gaya muku kawai, Firayim Minista, ku saurari mutane.
